    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose an ALMA observation to measure the line profile of [CII]158micron, 
which is redshifted to Band 8, of a powerful, Type II QSO at z=2.94 (COSMOS 
XID147) selected in the XMM-COSMOS survey. This X-ray selected galaxy hosts an 
heavily obscured active nucleus with a high accretion rate, which is likely to 
drive a powerful AGN-driven wind to clear the obscuring surrounding. Together 
with the intense star formation with ~1400 Msun/yr, this object belongs to the 
class of Hyper-luminous infrared galaxies. Strong far-infrared emission-line of 
[CII] is expected, and if a galaxy-wide feedback due to the AGN-driven wind is 
operating, then its line profile would be distorted, which we aim to measure. 
With the multi-wavelength datasets of COSMOS, XID147 is found to be one of the 
ideal target at the right epoch of the cosmic history (z~3) to search for 
observational signatures of AGN feedback at work.</prp:abstract>
